Good thank you. So the first question we've
got and are going to talk about is the racket

00:00:21.310 --> 00:00:28.080
height. So should the racket be the same height
as the ball or should it be lower than the

00:00:28.080 --> 00:00:31.600
ball? That's a question that we've been asked.
What do you make of that question Alois?

00:00:31.600 --> 00:00:37.540
What I think we're talking about here is the
racket height as you're hitting the ball so

00:00:37.540 --> 00:00:43.989
if you're going to play a topspin stroke,
then the bat needs to be a little bit below

00:00:43.989 --> 00:00:50.270
the ball so that it can come up on the ball
that way. If you're playing a backspin stroke

00:00:50.270 --> 00:00:57.110
then you can start a little bit above the
ball and come down to generate the backspin.

00:00:57.110 --> 00:01:02.690
Maybe for a serve is what she was talking
about. It's best to start either just a little

00:01:02.690 --> 00:01:08.450
bit above the ball so you can come down on
it that way or behind the ball so you come

00:01:08.450 --> 00:01:14.431
flat and into the ball that way as well. So
it depends on the type of spin that you are

00:01:14.431 --> 00:01:23.090
trying to produce, where the racket starts
in relation to the ball.

