it so he's got a bat with some rubber on it
so I think a Donic Coppa JO Gold and Mark

00:03:11.109 --> 00:03:16.980
V on the backhand but he can't control the
ball so his question is should he change his

00:03:16.980 --> 00:03:19.060
bat?

00:03:19.060 --> 00:03:22.469
I think he's also got an offensive blade as
well there.

00:03:22.469 --> 00:03:26.989
He does, yes it's a Donic Persson exclusive
offensive.

00:03:26.989 --> 00:03:33.150
Yep, so this is a problem we often find with
players and it's really natural when we start

00:03:33.150 --> 00:03:40.370
to play we want to get a good bat and it's
really difficult when you're starting to work

00:03:40.370 --> 00:03:46.079
out what is a good bat. I mean you look at
a bat that's $200 and think fantastic that's

00:03:46.079 --> 00:03:50.491
going to be the one for me but often when
you're starting it's really important to start

00:03:50.491 --> 00:03:59.189
with a lower speed bat and a bat with a bit
more control. So if you, it sounds like the

00:03:59.189 --> 00:04:04.489
bat that you've got there is just a little
bit too fast for you so you need to come back

00:04:04.489 --> 00:04:09.809
a step. Keep the bat, put it in your drawer,
or put it in the cupboard because hopefully

00:04:09.809 --> 00:04:15.630
as you progress that's a bat that you will
be able to use down the track. The bat that

00:04:15.630 --> 00:04:21.289
we recommend to start off with is the PingSkills
Rook which is just a good control bat but

00:04:21.289 --> 00:04:27.120
it has reasonable quality rubber on it as
well so you still want to have a bat that

00:04:27.120 --> 00:04:33.379
you can get a bit of grip and a bit of spin
on the ball but the bat that you have bought

00:04:33.379 --> 00:04:39.620
for yourself I think is just a bit too fast
so my advice is probably go for something

00:04:39.620 --> 00:04:46.110
a little bit slower, just a pre-made bat to
start off with and put the other one away

00:04:46.110 --> 00:04:47.830
till you get a little bit better.

00:04:47.830 --> 00:04:52.580
Yeah good advice. So it's really important
isn't it that you get something that is not

00:04:52.580 --> 00:04:58.270
too fast so that you can learn to play a full
stroke and learn to hit the ball consistently

00:04:58.270 --> 00:05:02.319
on the table. If the ball is coming off too
fast you're going to compromise your stroke,

00:05:02.319 --> 00:05:07.360
